statements: SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences;
SELECT gene_name, sequence_length FROM genetic_sequences;
SELECT sequence_id, gene_name, sequence_data FROM genetic_sequences;
SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences WHERE gene_name = 'ABC';
SELECT gene_name, sequence_length FROM genetic_sequences WHERE sequence_length < 1000;
SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences WHERE sequence_length > 100;
SELECT sequence_id, gene_name FROM genetic_sequences WHERE gene_name = 'ABC' AND sequence_length < 200;
SELECT sequence_id, sequence_length FROM genetic_sequences ORDER BY sequence_id DESC;
SELECT gene_name, COUNT(*) AS sequence_count FROM genetic_sequences GROUP BY gene_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;
SELECT DISTINCT gene_name FROM genetic_sequences WHERE sequence_length = (SELECT MAX(sequence_length) FROM genetic_sequences);
SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences WHERE organism_name = 'Human';
SELECT sequence_data, sequence_length FROM genetic_sequences ORDER BY sequence_length DESC;
SELECT organism_name, COUNT(*) FROM genetic_sequences GROUP BY organism_name;
SELECT sequence_id, analysis_type, analysis_result FROM analysis_results WHERE analysis_result != 'Failed';
SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences WHERE sequence_length > 1000 ORDER BY sequence_length ASC;
SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences ORDER BY organism_name ASC;
SELECT sequence_data, sequence_length FROM genetic_sequences WHERE sequence_length > 100;
SELECT * FROM genetic_sequences WHERE organism_name = 'Homo sapiens';
SELECT sequence_data, analysis_type FROM genetic_sequences JOIN analysis_results ON genetic_sequences.id = analysis_results.sequence_id;
SELECT organism_name, COUNT(*) FROM genetic_sequences GROUP BY organism_name;
SELECT id, dna_sequence, quality_score FROM genetic_data;
